# =============================================================================
# ZABR-008  Multilingual Legal Awareness Assistant  -  Environment Template
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# The application runs on Next.js + Convex. Environment lives in two places:
#
#   1. web/.env.local        - the frontend + CLI (written by `npx convex dev`)
#   2. the Convex deployment - server-side secrets (`npx convex env set ...`)
#
# NEVER commit real keys; only this template is tracked.
# =============================================================================


# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# web/.env.local  (frontend + operator scripts)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Written automatically by `npx convex dev` from web/:
# CONVEX_DEPLOYMENT=dev:your-deployment
# NEXT_PUBLIC_CONVEX_URL=https://your-deployment.convex.cloud

# Clerk (authentication) - get keys at https://dashboard.clerk.com
# NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=replace-with-clerk-publishable-key
# CLERK_SECRET_KEY=replace-with-clerk-secret-key
# NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_SIGN_IN_URL=/sign-in
# NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_SIGN_UP_URL=/sign-up

# For scripts/ingestLegalCorpus.ts and scripts/runGoldEval.ts (must match the
# values set on the Convex deployment below):
# INGEST_KEY=replace-with-strong-random-value
# EVAL_KEY=replace-with-strong-random-value
# LLM_API_KEY=replace-with-llm-api-key


# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Convex deployment env vars  (npx convex env set <NAME> <value>)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# CLERK_JWT_ISSUER_DOMAIN  - issuer URL of the Clerk "convex" JWT template
#                            (Clerk dashboard -> JWT templates -> Convex)
# CLERK_SECRET_KEY         - lets account deletion erase the Clerk user
#
# LLM (generation + intent extraction) - any OpenAI-compatible endpoint.
# Answering is live-only (ADR 0010): no key, no answers, never a fallback.
# NOTE: a free tier may use inputs to train the provider's model - this is
# disclosed in the user privacy notice. Move to a paid no-training tier for
# any real deployment.
# LLM_API_KEY   (required)
# LLM_MODEL     (required, e.g. gemini-2.5-flash)
# LLM_BASE_URL  (default https://generativelanguage.googleapis.com/v1beta/openai/)
#
# Embeddings - an OpenAI-compatible /embeddings endpoint. Defaults to the LLM
# provider and credential. Corpus embeddings are generated ONLY at ingest
# time and stored permanently; runtime embeds only the query.
# EMBEDDING_API_KEY   (optional, defaults to LLM_API_KEY)
# EMBEDDING_MODEL     (default gemini-embedding-001; 768 dimensions)
# EMBEDDING_BASE_URL  (optional, defaults to LLM_BASE_URL)
#
# Operator secrets (generate with:
#   python3 -c "import secrets; print(secrets.token_urlsafe(32))")
# INGEST_KEY  - authorises the corpus ingestion mutations
# EVAL_KEY    - authorises the live gold-eval action
